The maximum spot fine for the contravention of Level 4 water restrictions has been raised to R5,000. CAPE TOWN The City of Cape Town has warned repeat water wasters could face time behind bars.The municipality adds that it is lobbying the courts to back its move for harsher penalties and more intensive deterrents.The maximum spot fine for the contravention of Level 4 water restrictions has been raised to R5,000.The city s Zara Nicholson says: There is some rain predicted for this week. We need continuous rainfall for over many weeks for our dam levels to reach sufficient levels. We, therefore, appeal to residents and business to keep up the water saving measures and not to relax the efforts. 